# My Library header: identity row + divider (no pill, no collage)

Single cohesive surface and typography hierarchy. No giant dark pill, no book-cover collage.

---

## Theme behavior (tokens only, no per-screen hacks)

**Light mode:**
- **bg** — parchment/off-white
- **surface** — slightly warmer (not stark white)
- **text** — high contrast (textPrimary / textSecondary)

**Dark mode:**
- **bg** — deep charcoal
- **surface** — slightly lighter charcoal
- **text** — near-white
- **divider** — subtle but visible

Use **theme.colors.*** everywhere. No hardcoded colors for light/dark.

---

## Header layout

- **Container:** paddingTop safe area, paddingHorizontal 16, paddingBottom 12, backgroundColor: bg
- **Row 1 (identity):** Left: avatar monogram (40×40, surface) + name block (name 22 semibold textPrimary, username 15 medium textSecondary). Right: gear (36×36, surface, icon textPrimary). Gap 12. Compact.
- **Row 2 (optional):** Thin divider — height 1, color divider, marginTop 12

---

## Acceptance criteria

- Looks **premium and intentional** in both themes
- **No collage/covers** in header
- **No giant empty header space**
- **Name / @ readable** (typography hierarchy)
- **One-pane vibe** — no stack of random cards; single cohesive surface

---

## Do NOT

- Do NOT add a huge dark pill or full-width bar
- Do NOT add book-cover strip/collage to header
- Do NOT use hardcoded colors (e.g. rgba(0,0,0,0.55)) — use tokens
- Do NOT create giant empty header area
